summary: Licensed United Healthcare Insurance Sales Agent with a proven track record in sales, customer service, and building client relationships. Skilled in identifying customer needs, upselling and cross-selling health insurance products, meeting sales goals, and maintaining HIPAA compliance. Recognized with multiple awards for performance and client satisfaction.

experience.title: Licensed United Healthcare Insurance Sales Agent
experience.description: Provided services to clients changing or updating healthcare insurance needs by upselling/cross selling a variety of health insurance products (MA, MAPD, MED Sup and PDPs) to groups and individuals. Assisted with outbound campaigns, demonstrated prospecting skills, met or exceeded sales goals, delivered exceptional customer service, built new client relationships, and followed HIPAA guidelines and company policy.

experience.title: Account Executive Sales Agent / FedEx Account
experience.description: Maintained and deepened existing customer relations; made outbound calls to engage customers with new products and services; increased volume from existing customers; delivered client's family of services using consultative sales approach; built valued proposals and maintained established sales processes.

experience.title: Licensed United Healthcare Insurance Sales Agent
experience.description: Provided services to clients changing or updating healthcare insurance needs by upselling/cross selling health insurance products (MA, MAPD, MED Sup and PDPs) to groups and individual consumers; followed HIPAA guidelines; achieved sales goals; built rapport and trust with customers.

experience.title: Customer Service Agent
experience.description: Handled pharmacy/pharmacist contacts via telephone on insurance authorization, benefits, claims; adjudicated prescription claims; determined prior authorizations or overrides; adhered to HIPAA and CMS compliance and regulations; delivered exceptional customer service in a fast-paced environment.

experience.title: Customer Service Task Specialist
experience.description: Contacted creditors and new/existing clients daily to open/update accounts; negotiated terms; processed payments; educated clients on proposals; consistently met/exceeded quota goals of 200 inbound/outbound calls daily; collaborated with customer care departments and management.
